---
import BaseLayout from "../components/BaseLayout.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
import Header from "../components/Header.astro";
import WaitlistForm from "../components/WaitlistForm.astro";

const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.endsWith("/") ? import.meta.env.BASE_URL : `${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/`;
const heroImage = `${base}images/hull-leak-monitor-hero.jpeg`;
---

<BaseLayout
  description="Hull Leak Monitor is a panel-mounted DC leakage monitor for aluminium and steel boats, designed to track battery-to-hull leakage trends and help troubleshoot suspect circuits."
>
  <Header />

  <main>
    <section class="overflow-hidden bg-[#eef2ed]">
      <div class="section-shell grid gap-9 py-10 sm:py-12 lg:grid-cols-[0.78fr_1.22fr] lg:items-center lg:gap-10 lg:py-14">
        <div class="max-w-xl">
          <p class="eyebrow">DC leakage monitoring for metal-hull boats</p>
          <h1 class="mt-2 text-5xl font-semibold leading-[0.95] text-ink sm:text-6xl">
            Hull Leak Monitor
          </h1>
          <p class="mt-6 text-lg leading-8 text-ink/72 sm:text-xl sm:leading-9">
            Monitor up to 4 battery banks, get historic trends and automatic alerts, and use continuous debug mode to help find the circuit causing the problem.
          </p>
          <div class="mt-8 flex flex-col gap-3 sm:flex-row">
            <a
              class="inline-flex min-h-12 items-center justify-center rounded-md bg-ink px-5 text-base font-semibold text-white shadow-sm transition hover:bg-panel-black"
              href="#waitlist"
            >
              Join the waitlist
            </a>
            <a
              class="inline-flex min-h-12 items-center justify-center rounded-md border border-ink/18 bg-white/80 px-5 text-base font-semibold text-ink shadow-sm transition hover:bg-white"
              href="#how-it-works"
            >
              See how it works
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>

        <figure class="lg:justify-self-end">
          <img
            class="block w-full max-w-3xl"
            src={heroImage}
            alt="Front view product mockup of the Hull Leak Monitor panel with LCD readings and leakage level indicator lights."
            loading="eager"
          />
        </figure>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="how-it-works" class="bg-white py-16 sm:py-20">
      <div class="section-shell">
        <div class="max-w-3xl">
          <p class="eyebrow">How it works</p>
          <h2 class="mt-4 text-3xl font-semibold leading-tight text-ink sm:text-4xl">
            Scans up to 4 battery banks for DC hull leaks.
          </h2>
          <p class="mt-5 leading-8 text-ink/68">
            Hull Leak Monitor checks the positive and negative side of each battery bank against the hull reference, logs numerical readings, and keeps simple panel status visible through the LCD and leakage level LEDs.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="mt-10 grid gap-4 lg:grid-cols-3">
          <article class="rounded-lg border border-ink/10 bg-mist p-6">
            <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-copper">Peace of mind, without remembering to use the tester.</p>
            <h3 class="mt-3 text-xl font-semibold text-ink">Automatic periodic scanning</h3>
            <p class="mt-3 leading-7 text-ink/68">
          Install the device and forget about it.</br>
            In monitoring mode, the device wakes at the configured interval, such as every hour, scans all battery banks for leaks, stores the readings, updates status LEDs, and if necessary raises an alert by email, sounds a buzzer, or activate an external relay if configured.
            </p>
          </article>
          <article class="rounded-lg border border-ink/10 bg-mist p-6">
            <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-copper">Actual trends, no more wondering when it started.</p>
            <h3 class="mt-3 text-xl font-semibold text-ink">History instead of one-off checks</h3>
            <p class="mt-3 leading-7 text-ink/68">
              Traditional indicators show the present condition. Logged trends help owners see whether a conductor is stable, slowly changing, or moving during solar panel operation, shore-power use, or heavy rain.
            </p>
          </article>
          <article class="rounded-lg border border-ink/10 bg-mist p-6">
            <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-copper">Actual Ohm values and sound feedback while you work.</p>
            <h3 class="mt-3 text-xl font-semibold text-ink">Continuous troubleshooting mode</h3>
            <p class="mt-3 leading-7 text-ink/68">
              Select one battery terminal and watch the live value change as you work. Fixing one leak in presence of another has a noticeable effect, contrary to pure LED-based monitors.<br/>
              Higher and lower beeps keep you aware of changes while you are working deep in the hull, without calling the wife to give you readings back to the panel.
            </p>
          </article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>


    <section id="specs" class="bg-mist py-16 sm:py-20">
      <div class="section-shell">
        <div class="max-w-3xl">
          <p class="eyebrow">Capabilities</p>
          <h2 class="mt-4 text-3xl font-semibold leading-tight text-ink sm:text-4xl">
            Key specifications.
          </h2>
        </div>

        <ul class="mt-10 grid gap-3 sm:grid-cols-2">
          <li class="rounded-lg border border-ink/10 bg-white p-4 leading-7 text-ink/72 shadow-lift">
            <span class="font-semibold text-ink">Power input:</span> 12 V or 24 V DC, reverse-polarity protected.
          </li>
          <li class="rounded-lg border border-ink/10 bg-white p-4 leading-7 text-ink/72 shadow-lift">
            <span class="font-semibold text-ink">Battery monitoring:</span> up to 4 battery banks, positive and negative, for 8 monitored wires.
          </li>
          <li class="rounded-lg border border-ink/10 bg-white p-4 leading-7 text-ink/72 shadow-lift">
            <span class="font-semibold text-ink">Automated scans:</span> periodic scan interval is adjustable (between one hour and off).
          </li>
          <li class="rounded-lg border border-ink/10 bg-white p-4 leading-7 text-ink/72 shadow-lift">
            <span class="font-semibold text-ink">Alerts:</span> sound alerts (with sound off switch), email alerts if Wi-Fi is set up, and external relay output.
          </li>
          <li class="rounded-lg border border-ink/10 bg-white p-4 leading-7 text-ink/72 shadow-lift">
            <span class="font-semibold text-ink">Controls:</span> LCD plus joystick for configuration and readings.
          </li>
          <li class="rounded-lg border border-ink/10 bg-white p-4 leading-7 text-ink/72 shadow-lift">
            <span class="font-semibold text-ink">Status LEDs:</span> basic operation, power, and alert indication.
          </li>
             <li class="rounded-lg border border-ink/10 bg-white p-4 leading-7 text-ink/72 shadow-lift">
            <span class="font-semibold text-ink">Wifi:</span> Can either connect to the boat's network, or act as a hotspot to which you can connect
          </li>
           </li>
             <li class="rounded-lg border border-ink/10 bg-white p-4 leading-7 text-ink/72 shadow-lift">
            <span class="font-semibold text-ink">Web Portal:</span> Visualize your data or download it as a .csv text file
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="waitlist" class="bg-white py-16 sm:py-20">
      <div class="section-shell grid gap-10 lg:grid-cols-[0.9fr_1.1fr] lg:items-start">
        <div>
          <p class="eyebrow">Join the waitlist</p>
          <h2 class="mt-4 text-3xl font-semibold leading-tight text-ink sm:text-4xl">
            Get product updates and launch news.
          </h2>
          <p class="mt-5 leading-8 text-ink/68">
            Join the waitlist for updates, installation notes, and early availability announcements.
          </p>
        </div>

        <WaitlistForm />
      </div>
    </section>
        <section class="bg-panel-black py-16 text-white sm:py-20">
      <div class="section-shell">
        <div class="rounded-lg border border-white/12 bg-white/[0.04] p-5 sm:p-6">
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-warning">Important note</p>
          <p class="mt-3 leading-7 text-white/68">
            Hull Leak Monitor is a monitoring tool and diagnostic aid for aluminium and steel boats. It supports troubleshooting, but it is not a replacement for a qualified marine electrician.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

  </main>

  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>
